children.content: a Business Capability is the higher, stable, abstract concept of what a business does (e.g. Marketing, Sales, etc.) - independent of the organization's structure, processes, people, or domains.

The non-functional capabilities refer to characteristics of services that do not relate to their functional capabilities. The functional capabilities refer to the what functions the service is supposed to perform. The non-functional capabilities help in assessing how well the service performs these functions. The non-functional capabilities are usually the quality attributes of the service such as reliability, security, response-time etc.
